post_text:
Greetings Falcon family!

This has been an eventful day!!! To the parents who called with encouraging words for us, we thank you and WE LOVE YOU! Here are some takeaways ‚Äì we are still working through log in issues continue to call us if you experience them and we will work through it together.
This first week will be focused on adjusting to this format, logging in to the different classes and learning how online etiquette works for us falcons. Also, we have food resources available for our families. Tuesdays and Thursdays stop up between the hours of 11 AM to 1 PM to receive breakfast and lunch to take home for our scholars.
Please make sure we have the most up to date phone & email information for you. Check your emails for updates often ‚Äì never forget we are in this together!!

Falcon Strong - Principal D

Falcons are members of the community we serve, teach, meet with on a daily basis. As racism and xenophobia become more prevalent and overt in our schools and communities, it is more important than ever to listen to and elevate the voices, experiences, and history of our fellow citizens and communities under attack.

Lake Erie Prep is here to be a part of the conversation on how we can work to make this a better place for our scholars and their families. We are committed to the fight of education for all.

Falcon Strong

post_text:
Falcon Strong

This year has brought its share of ups and downs , surprises and challenges . One thing that remained consistent was our sense of duty to our scholars and overall sense of family and community .

From the first day of school to the last our falcons from the oldest to youngest guide our thoughts and actions . No one school is perfect and we are far from it . Yet , we strive to continually uphold the expectations of Respect-Responsibility- Relentlessness; to keep our eye on the goal of education for all .

Our 8th grade falcons will leave our nest today and begin their next phase at various high schools through out the county . Our youngest falcons made a HUGE step from kindergarten to First grade .

We stopped by each and every one of their homes today to congratulate them!

Tears -smiles -laughter and love were in abundance.

Falcon Strong

Principal D

(Here are a few snapshots - enjoy !)

post_text:
FALCON MEMO ‚Äì Week of 05/17/20
Falcon Families

PILLARS are used as a support or foundation structure for a building. They are what keeps a building standing. At LEP we believe in the Three Pillars ~ RESPECT ‚Äì RESPONSIBILITY ‚Äì RELENTLESSNESS. Without them our foundation would not stand the test of challenges and obstacles that life places in our path.

Respect ‚Äì Treat others the way you want to be treated.
Responsibility ‚Äì Do what you HAVE to do now to do what you want to do later.

text:
FALCON MEMO ‚Äì Week of 05/17/20
Falcon Families

PILLARS are used as a support or foundation structure for a building. They are what keeps a building standing. At LEP we believe in the Three Pillars ~ RESPECT ‚Äì RESPONSIBILITY ‚Äì RELENTLESSNESS. Without them our foundation would not stand the test of challenges and obstacles that life places in our path.

Respect ‚Äì Treat others the way you want to be treated.
Responsibility ‚Äì Do what you HAVE to do now to do what you want to do later.
Relentlessness ‚Äì Never give up!

These pillars support our overall mission of life beyond High school and College. The skill sets that we help to instill in our scholars will hopefully stick with them‚Ä¶
